revenue.bio: CASH MONEY - If you prefer cannabis' therapeutic effects -- calming, pain management, anti-anxiety -- more than its heady, trippy aspects, you have many options with products high in CBD and low in THC.
revenue.strains: Restore, BrainPower, Complete in Oils, Extracts, and Capsules

ego.bio: EGO FEED - CBD products are organic, natural, and legal to buy in every state. CBD has therapeutic effects -- calming, pain management, anti-anxiety -- and also helps protect against bone loss and osteoporosis.

adjacency.bio: THE HALO - CBD products can be vaped, mixed with food, swallowed, and even applied topically. A great way to relax is with a tea containing CBD at night time.
adjacency.strains: Capsules, Extract, topical Shea Butter Creme

Courtney.bio: Courtney, 29, is a paralegal in Charlotte, N.C. She’s engaged to her high school sweetheart. She’s a budding oenophile.
Courtney.strains: Courtney loves her Samsung Galaxy, and uses it mostly to play games and watch YouTube videos. She’s a whiz at Excel and searching Westlaw.
Courtney.sponsorTagline: Mondo is an all-natural powder made from Blue Dream flowers

Alice.bio: Alice is a 34-year-old divorced single mother who just moved from Chicago to Phoenix with her teenage son. Her job as a waitress takes up most of her time, but she loves her weekly bowling league.
Alice.strains: Alice’s only computer is a cranky Dell she bought in 2011. She loves her iPod, but it doesn’t have enough memory for music and apps, so she sticks to music.

Edie.bio: Edie is a regular commenter on a major media site’s advice column. She’s 55, married, and works part-time as a bank teller in Ann Arbor, Mich. She enjoys quilting, photography, and pampering her poodle.
Edie.strains: Edie knows her way around her MacBook, but would have to Google how to clear her browser cookies.

Adeline.bio: Adeline is a 48 year-old architect in Charleston, South Carolina. She’s married with two children, and she spends every weekend she can on her family’s sailboat. The ocean breezes calm her.
Adeline.strains: Adeline could teach a master class in Adobe Illustrator, but she gets frustrated with some websites. She’d make a convincing argument that two-factor authentication is the devil’s work.
